{"title_en":"First Nipah virus death of the year recorded in Bangladesh","title_bn":"???? ????? ??????? ???? ????? ????? ??????","summary_en":"A child in Manikganj has died after contracting the Nipah virus from raw date juice, marking the first such fatality in the country this year.","summary_bn":"?????????? ????? ??????? ?? ??? ??? ?? ????? ?????? ?????, ?? ???? ???? ???? ????? ??????? ????? ?????? ?????? ?????? ??? ??????","body_en":"Bangladesh has recorded its first death from the Nipah virus in 2024. The victim, a child from Manikganj, passed away while undergoing treatment at a hospital in Dhaka. Health officials from the Institute of Epidemiology, Disease Control and Research (IEDCR) confirmed that the child was infected after consuming raw date juice. The IEDCR has issued a high alert, urging citizens to avoid drinking raw date juice as it is often contaminated with the saliva or excreta of infected fruit bats, the primary carriers of the virus.","body_bn":"???? ???? ???? ????? ??????? ????? ??????? ???? ?????? ??????????? ?? ???? ?????? ?????????? ??????? ???? ???? ??????? ?????????, ??? ????????? ? ?????? ?????????? (?????????) ??????? ????? ??, ?????? ????? ??????? ?? ??? ???? ??????? ????? ??????? ???????? ??????? ????????? ?????? ??????? ????? ??????? ?? ??? ??? ???? ???? ????? ???? ????? ??????? ???? ?????, ???? ??????? ???? ?? ????????? ??????? ?? ?????? ????? ?????","image_prompt_en":"A realistic image of a traditional clay pot tied to a date palm tree in a rural Bangladeshi village at dawn, symbolizing the collection of date juice, with a medical mask and a warning sign overlay.","image_prompt_bn":"??????? ?????????? ???? ??????? ??????? ????? ???? ????? ?????????? ????? ?????? ??????????? ???, ???? ???? ????? ??? ????????? ??????? ??????? ??????","category":"World","tags":["Nipah Virus","Bangladesh Health","IEDCR","Manikganj","Public Health Alert"],"sentiment":"Negative","tone":"Informative","author":"Ahnaf Hassan Aurnil","source":"Shomoy Tv","tim